<subSubSection id="F4C86558BD5CFF929EDFFC38DDFFDE8B" pageId="9" pageNumber="536" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="BC6D36D3BD5CFF929EDFFC38DDFFDE8B" blockId="9.[151,1437,957,1200]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">
<emphasis id="8EA6EAC1BD5CFF929EDFFC38DE4FD9F3" bold="true" box="[151,274,957,983]" pageId="9" pageNumber="536">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Head lenticular, covered with short silvery pubescence; temple narrow; eyes strongly indented opposite antennal sockets; clypeus a little convex to strongly convex, its apical margin broadly rounded; mandible with lamella; mandible with teeth equal or subequal; malar space 0.35–0.60× basal width of mandible; central 0.3 of mesopleuron furrow not impressed; epicnemial carina extending slightly more than 0.5 height of mesopleuron; propodeum with a median groove; fore wing areolet small with a very long petiole, sometimes absent, second discoidal cell acute; hind wing CU&amp;cu-a vein broken at its lower 0.25–0.33; hind tarsal claw pectinate; first metasomal segment with suture separating sternite from tergite dorsally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
